        <h2>Impact of Padding and Margin</h2>
        <p>
            CSS properties like <strong>padding</strong> and <strong>margin</strong> have a significant impact on the layout and spacing of elements within a webpage. 
            They control how elements are positioned relative to each other and the space around them.
        </p>
        <!-- Brief Example of Padding and Margin -->
        <h3>Example of Padding</h3>
        <p>
            The <strong>padding</strong> property controls the space between the content of an element and its border. 
            It doesn't affect the element's outer dimensions (width and height) but affects the inner space.
        </p>
